OL,6,FShe said at Cabinet, ministers took
OL,7,Fcollective responsibility for
OL,8,Fdecisions even if they disagreed with
OL,9,Fthem. She reflected on her time
OL,10,Fworking in the Cabinet Office during
OL,11,Fthe Conservative/Liberal Democrat
OL,12,Fcoalition and said when ministers from
OL,13,Fthe different parties disagreed on an
OL,14,Fissue there was a set process on how
OL,15,Fto deal with that which allowed prime
OL,16,Fminister David Cameron and deputy
OL,17,Fprime minister Nick Clegg to express
OL,18,Ftheir different views in Parliament.
